  "prompt": "What is the meaning of stress?",
  "response": "Stress refers to the body's reaction to any change that requires an adjustment or response. It can manifest physically, emotionally, or mentally, and is a normal part of life. Stress can be triggered by a variety of factors, such as daily responsibilities, major life changes, or external events. While small amounts of stress can be motivating and beneficial, chronic or excessive stress can lead to negative health outcomes, including anxiety, depression, and physical ailments.",
